1
00:00:05,460 --> 00:00:10,750
Forty five thousand one hundred forty five sheep.

2
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:16,400
Forty five thousand one hundred forty six sheep.

3
00:00:17,610 --> 00:00:22,980
Forty five thousand one hundred forty seven sheep.

4
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:28,510
Forty five thousand one hundred forty nine sheep.

5
00:00:28,510 --> 00:00:33,230
Fort— no, one hundred forty eight sheep.

6
00:00:33,230 --> 00:00:39,340
Forty five thousand five... five hundred...

7
00:00:44,730 --> 00:00:46,830
I'm going to go crazy.

8
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,790
It's three o'clock.

9
00:00:56,930 --> 00:01:00,300
Jae Hyeong, are you sleeping?

10
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,630
If you're awake, can I call you?

11
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:18,550
I feel sleepy. I feel sleepy. I feel sleepy. I feel sleepy.

12
00:01:18,550 --> 00:01:24,000
It's coming! It's coming. It's coming. It's coming.

13
00:01:26,030 --> 00:01:30,590
Someone help me fall asleep!

14
00:01:33,730 --> 00:01:41,890
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

15
00:02:09,390 --> 00:02:12,690
There are two kinds of people in this world.

16
00:02:12,690 --> 00:02:17,680
There are people who trip and fall, only to land on flower roads.

17
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:24,300
And those who flounder and fall on their faces into a smelly cesspool.

18
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:30,900
As for me, if you want to know ... it's every day, always in the cesspool.

19
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:36,830
Excuse me, ma'am! You don't plan on jumping from there, do you?

20
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:41,140
Nobody believes me. I'm going to jump!

21
00:02:41,140 --> 00:02:44,540
I'm going to jump off and die!

22
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:49,300
Ma'am, I'm the substitute driver you called for.

23
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:53,050
I'm not even a family member, so why are you trying to throw your life away in front of me?

24
00:02:53,050 --> 00:02:57,740
My whole life, I've done nothing but play piano,

25
00:02:57,740 --> 00:03:03,360
but I got fired from the orchestra today.

26
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:06,140
Orche-Orchestra?

27
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:10,970
Sinyeong Philharmonic

28
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:14,210
Pianist Gong Seon Mi.

29
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:15,550
The pianist of Sinyeong Philharmonic!

30
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:21,100
Yes. I am Gong Song Mi, Sinyeong Philharmonic pianist.

31
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:25,760
I've only played piano for 35 years, since I was seven!

32
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:31,200
The new conductor who arrived today, who has nothing but a pretty face, fired me.

33
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:40,030
Nam Ju Wan! You mean bastard!

34
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:42,870
Even if I die, I will curse you!

35
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:47,040
Ma'am!

36
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:56,290
Oh no! What do I do? Ma'am?

37
00:03:56,290 --> 00:03:57,830
What do I do?

38
00:05:24,010 --> 00:05:26,060
Thank you.

39
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:31,350
On this wonderful evening, I have a bit of sad news to share with you all.

40
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:37,550
After tonight's performance, I will bid farewell to the Sinyeong Philharmonic.

41
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:45,780
However, for the position I am vacating,

42
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:51,650
I will introduce another conductor, who will make our wonderful orchestra even more wonderful.

43
00:05:51,650 --> 00:05:55,090
He is already receiving love from many people.

44
00:05:55,090 --> 00:05:57,480
The maestro of passion,

45
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,500
Nam Ju Wan.

46
00:06:30,380 --> 00:06:33,900
It's nice to meet all of you. I'm Nam Ju Wan.

47
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:43,530
There is a man I have admired since I was a little boy.

48
00:06:43,530 --> 00:06:47,890
My teacher and current leader of the Philharmonic,

49
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:50,630
Maestro Song Jae Hwan.

50
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:06,000
In honor of my debut, Maestro Song Jae Hwan gave me a baton as a gift.

51
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:49,370
Thank you.

52
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:54,360
I, Nam Ju Wan, with these talented musicians here,

53
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:57,640
will make a wonderful, charming orchestra

54
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:00,850
that can make your heart flutter.

55
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:03,640
Please show us a lot of love and support.

56
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,100
I'm so cold.

57
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:36,160
Hello? Is your performance over?

58
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:40,020
Where are you? Come quickly to the green room.

59
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,700
I can't come.

60
00:08:43,270 --> 00:08:45,180
What? Why?

61
00:08:45,180 --> 00:08:47,140
You said you'd come right after your job.

62
00:08:47,140 --> 00:08:49,730
Do I have the type of life that goes smoothly?

63
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:53,960
I left  Manwong-Dong  to go to the Han River parking lot  on a 15,000-won (about $12)  call,

64
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:57,500
but the customer who called me jumped into Han River.

65
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:01,550
Han River? Is she crazy?

66
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,510
Who?

67
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:08,260
The pianist who got fired today...

68
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:12,600
Sunbae Seon Mi?

69
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,550
That's crazy. What happened?

70
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:27,970
I also jumped in to save her and got rescued by 911.

71
00:09:27,970 --> 00:09:31,160
Why would someone who can't even swim jump into the Han River?

72
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:36,050
Hey, someone jumped in the water, how could I stay still?

73
00:09:36,050 --> 00:09:37,970
When I came to my senses, I was in the water.

74
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:41,660
So, is Sunbae Seon Mi alright?

75
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:44,360
Yeah, I saw her get in the ambulance and I'm walking home right now.

76
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:48,140
I am so upset. I couldn't even get paid.

77
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:53,460
The driver agency already took out 3,600 won  for itself and 650 won for insurance from my account.

78
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:56,970
You know how it goes.  How can the world be so tough on me?

79
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:00,600
You almost died, is that stuff important right now?

80
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,270
That's why I said to just come to the performance.

81
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,890
Why did you go work as a driver?

82
00:10:04,890 --> 00:10:08,120
I should earn as much money as I can.

83
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:13,400
You're a tenured member of the orchestra. You don't understand the hellish life I'm living.

84
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:16,140
This place isn't exactly heaven, either.

85
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:19,540
Since your day's already ruined, you should come by to see the new maestro.

86
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:21,380
We're having a welcome party.

87
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:22,690
I'm not in the mood.

88
00:10:22,690 --> 00:10:26,560
Do moods fill your stomach? You need to let loose at times like these.

89
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:33,350
You did well today.

90
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:36,590
Hey, hey, hey, he's here.

91
00:10:36,590 --> 00:10:38,760
Don't bother arguing and get here fast.

92
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:42,660
He has a terrible temper but is the sexiest man I've ever seen.

93
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:44,740
You were a little surprised, right?

94
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:46,420
Were you alright?

95
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:49,500
It's fine. I'm not even a member, how could I come?

96
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:52,370
We should meet tomorrow if you have time.

97
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:04,280
Here are Maestro Nam's lips. I hope my gift will encourage you.

98
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:07,080
Use this for your insomnia. Ha ha ha.

99
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:12,200
This girl... She's only learned bad things.

100
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:19,820
What is this?

101
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:22,000
Damn it.

102
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:35,880
- It'll be 11,500 won (about $9.50).
- What? Oh.

103
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:40,180
Sorry but if you leave out the umbrella, how much is it?

104
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:42,810
5,500 won (about $4.50).

105
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,160
It's raining like crazy.

106
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:08,960
This fine dust sure is no joke today.

107
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:15,200
What?

108
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:18,800
What did you just say to me?

109
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,500
The fine dust is mixed into the rain.

110
00:12:25,290 --> 00:12:28,540
Do you need this? Take it.

111
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,710
- Your umbrella?
- Yep.

112
00:12:30,710 --> 00:12:34,130
Why would I? Do you know me or something?

113
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:38,790
- No, not really.
- Then why are you giving me your umbrella?

114
00:12:39,810 --> 00:12:43,260
It doesn't matter if I get hit with rain.

115
00:12:45,170 --> 00:12:50,330
You were going to buy an umbrella before, but you took it out. Just take this one and go.

116
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:06,130
Oh just a moment! Wait!

117
00:13:06,130 --> 00:13:08,690
Oh my!

118
00:13:08,690 --> 00:13:11,740
Take this back, please.

119
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:16,420
I'm grateful, but I don't accept favors from strangers.

120
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:18,930
Thank you!

121
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,350
Are you alright?

122
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:15,730
I swear,  what I'm going to talk about starting now is NOT love.

123
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:20,690
Where were you looking? You almost died, you know that?

124
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:42,790
Why? What's wrong?

125
00:14:44,770 --> 00:14:49,970
Look here, calm down.

126
00:14:55,620 --> 00:15:00,910
Hey, are you alright? What's wrong?

127
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:08,410
Once more, I swear,  what I'm going to talk about starting now is NOT love.

128
00:15:08,410 --> 00:15:11,780
It's a story about a sort of journey.

129
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:19,180
Dark, indistinct and harsh.  A journey in which I went in search of my memory.

130
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:24,460
I Wanna Hear Your Song

131
00:15:25,710 --> 00:15:30,100
Episode 1

132
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:34,840
Who is it? Eonni?

133
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:39,290
Good going.  Flabberghasting someone in the middle of the night.

134
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:44,040
What are you doing? Hurry up and get up!

135
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:50,730
I'm up now. You keep going around hitting  people.

136
00:15:57,550 --> 00:16:03,070
- Did I sleep here last night?
- Leave quietly without waking up the interns. They worked all night.

137
00:16:09,830 --> 00:16:14,380
A musician who doesn't even know her mallets are missing. Here.

138
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:19,450
Yesterday, there was some guy who brought you here and took care of them.

139
00:16:19,450 --> 00:16:22,510
The man who brought me here?  He took care of these?

140
00:16:22,510 --> 00:16:27,580
He was afraid the mallets would get warped from the rain so he put them in his own bag.

141
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:34,120
Who is this person who knows everything?  Was he a musician?

142
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:38,040
Did I at least get his phone number?

143
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:47,590
Don't be concerned about another man.  Just take good care of your boyfriend, that idiot.

144
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:51,370
Why are you talking about Jae Hyeong here?   Did my Jae Hyeong do something wrong?

145
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:56,170
If he doesn't cheat on you in one month, then I'll quit my job here.

146
00:16:56,170 --> 00:17:01,570
Did someone say something that you would be criticizing him? What? What?

147
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:05,840
I'm the only one in his heart.

148
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:10,430
SY Arts Center

149
00:17:11,060 --> 00:17:13,480
Daniel Redkovich
Live in Korea

150
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:24,600
Yu Da's new post is up.

151
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,710
Yu Da's new post is up.

152
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:34,200
Shocking news!
The fired pianist Gong Seon Mi jumped into the Han River.

153
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:38,840
Who could have been the person who pushed her to want to commit suicide, after a 15-year career in the orchestra?

154
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:42,750
You and I could become like her.

155
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:47,400
Wow, Yu Da is really something.

156
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:51,080
This is going to create a ruckus.

157
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:05,450
What's going on here?

158
00:18:11,650 --> 00:18:16,830
Yeah, the young suffer while living.  I might as well eat something.

159
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:22,730
Even if it's just this. ♫ Tuna and mayo...

160
00:18:24,330 --> 00:18:26,930
Yum, this is pretty good.

161
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:34,590
What?

162
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:36,980
Hey, where are you right now?

163
00:18:36,980 --> 00:18:39,580
Me? I'm at the music school. Why?

164
00:18:39,580 --> 00:18:42,400
Your lesson is not important now.  Maestro Nam is holding an audition.

165
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:46,300
I thought it was for the piano, but today he's looking for a percussionist.

166
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:50,580
- Really?
- I told you.  Maestro Nam is driven.

167
00:18:50,580 --> 00:18:54,540
The audition just started, so come quickly.

168
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:26,300
- What color does it sound like to you?
- What?

169
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:32,130
This performance is green, blue, yellow or orange?

170
00:19:32,130 --> 00:19:36,960
Um... well...

171
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:42,320
- Orange?
- Orange? I see.

172
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:45,750
You worked hard. Next.

173
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:00,780
Taxi!

174
00:20:23,580 --> 00:20:27,180
You worked hard. Next one!

175
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,790
Mister! Hurry up!

176
00:20:30,790 --> 00:20:33,690
We could die, do you want to die?

177
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:37,170
If I don't go, I'll die anyway!

178
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:40,640
Is he crazy? Why a percussionnist?

179
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:43,350
Right? Should we complain to the company?

180
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:46,760
And if you are fired like Su Mi, will you jump into Han River too?

181
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:49,140
What is this? Gosh!

182
00:21:00,430 --> 00:21:04,520
What's going on? The audition is not over yet, right?

183
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:07,820
Speak softly. Everyone is in a bad mood.

184
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:13,180
They are not happy about this audition and someone posted a picture of Su Mi at the hospital.

185
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:15,720
Really?

186
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:19,910
Even so, it's a good opportunity for you, so just think that you will do your best.

187
00:21:19,910 --> 00:21:24,620
I just asked Dal Hae to put your name on the audition list. You just need to wait your turn in the waiting room.

188
00:21:24,620 --> 00:21:29,520
Here, here! The performance is starting. Everyone, come out.

189
00:21:30,450 --> 00:21:34,090
Don't be nervous. Do just as we practiced. Got it?

190
00:21:34,090 --> 00:21:37,670
Don't worry. I'm betting my life on this one.

191
00:21:37,670 --> 00:21:40,440
No, I must bet my life on this one.

192
00:21:55,830 --> 00:21:57,980
Just a moment.

193
00:21:59,570 --> 00:22:02,560
Sinyeong Philharmonic Orchestra

194
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:06,130
When I was 20, life was easy.

195
00:22:09,130 --> 00:22:16,560
Now I lead a ragged existence, having to wait for someone else's decision.

196
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:22,510
Although art is as beautiful as a dream,

197
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:25,540
reality, in the end, is an infinite jungle,

198
00:22:25,540 --> 00:22:28,160
dependent on being chosen or not.

199
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:30,470
It is neither more nor less than that.

200
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:33,900
Thank you. Next!

201
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:49,040
Don't be nervous.

202
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,870
Anyway, life is a reality.

203
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:57,360
I have been unemployed for so long. But today, without a doubt, I will be the  chosen one.

204
00:24:23,180 --> 00:24:26,230
I like her playing.

205
00:24:26,230 --> 00:24:30,190
Maybe she needs to control her strength more, what do you think?

206
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:49,440
Hong Yi Yeong?

207
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:53,970
It's blood!

208
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:06,010
You are really something else!

209
00:26:06,010 --> 00:26:09,780
How stupid are you to lose your mallet during an audition?

210
00:26:19,550 --> 00:26:21,570
Idiot!

211
00:26:21,570 --> 00:26:24,430
I practiced that so many times.

212
00:26:24,430 --> 00:26:29,290
Why, of all times,  did I have to accidentally drop my mallet?

213
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:44,910
How did the audition go?

214
00:26:44,910 --> 00:26:47,780
Why haven't you contacted me?

215
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:53,940
I'm sorry, I'll call you tomorrow.

216
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:25,500
Jae Hyeong, are you sleeping?

217
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:29,940
Since this evening, I've called you many times, but you did not answer.

218
00:27:29,940 --> 00:27:34,260
I want to hear your voice so badly I could die.

219
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:38,670
Can't I call you now?

220
00:27:57,550 --> 00:28:00,700
Your sigh will wake up the neighborhood.

221
00:28:03,190 --> 00:28:08,680
For it to be tasty, you have to add the egg when the noodles are almost done.

222
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:11,660
You know nothing about life.

223
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:16,210
Look here, mister. How does it matter to you when I put in my egg?

224
00:28:16,210 --> 00:28:19,700
Don't talk about my life when we aren't even acq—

225
00:28:24,690 --> 00:28:27,060
Do you need this? Take it.

226
00:28:27,060 --> 00:28:27,820
Do you know me or something?

227
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:30,080
No, not really.

228
00:28:32,060 --> 00:28:35,560
Where were you looking? You almost died, you know that?

229
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:45,470
Cheese or kimchi?

230
00:28:45,470 --> 00:28:46,320
What?

231
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:48,410
Do you eat ramyeon...

232
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:53,570
Do you eat ramyeon with cheese or kimchi?

233
00:28:53,570 --> 00:28:56,410
Ramyeon with... kimchi.

234
00:28:56,410 --> 00:28:59,160
Okay. So kimchi it is. Deal!

235
00:29:01,580 --> 00:29:03,150
What do you want?

236
00:29:03,150 --> 00:29:05,650
You're so slow-minded!

237
00:29:05,650 --> 00:29:08,360
You do not like to be indebted to people, right?

238
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:12,600
But that day, I helped you, right?

239
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,880
- So what?
- Pay it back with kimchi.

240
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:17,690
Stir-fried kimchi, okay?

241
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:25,610
And buy fried rice with ham and cheese. Put it three minutes in the microwave.

242
00:29:33,070 --> 00:29:36,760
Fried rice with ham and cheese. Stir-fried kimchi.

243
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:38,680
All good, right?

244
00:29:39,430 --> 00:29:41,740
You understand me.

245
00:29:53,730 --> 00:29:58,290
You don't look happy today. Something bad happened to you?

246
00:29:58,290 --> 00:30:01,530
How does this concern you?

247
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:06,060
Mind your own business.

248
00:30:06,060 --> 00:30:10,930
I'm not really a stranger. I saved your life, as you remember.

249
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:13,140
You saved my life?

250
00:30:13,140 --> 00:30:16,430
Yes, I did. I saved you.

251
00:30:17,860 --> 00:30:23,230
But, you are eating ramyeon at past 3 a.m. You've given up on your diet.

252
00:30:23,230 --> 00:30:24,890
Did you break up with your boyfriend?

253
00:30:24,890 --> 00:30:29,330
Or did someone defraud you of your money?

254
00:30:29,330 --> 00:30:31,830
Enough now.

255
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:34,020
Are you making a joke of me?

256
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:36,000
I'm seducing you.

257
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:36,910
Oh, this person is strange!

258
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:39,170
This person?

259
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:44,190
You curse me with this face.

260
00:30:44,190 --> 00:30:46,160
You are scary.

261
00:30:50,660 --> 00:30:52,520
Where are you going?

262
00:31:00,550 --> 00:31:02,420
Here.

263
00:31:08,290 --> 00:31:10,550
010-646-0281

264
00:31:10,550 --> 00:31:11,510
What is this?

265
00:31:11,510 --> 00:31:13,560
My phone number.

266
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:20,030
I know I should not write it on money but you will not throw a bill away.

267
00:31:21,060 --> 00:31:27,370
Do not misunderstand me, I'm not into you. I'm looking for a part-time job.

268
00:31:27,370 --> 00:31:28,180
Part-time job?

269
00:31:28,180 --> 00:31:29,400
Yes, part-time job.

270
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:33,160
I can do commissions. The things you need when living alone.

271
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:37,500
For example, someone to carry heavy things.

272
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:42,300
Someone to buy medecine when you are sick. Throw out the trash.

273
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:47,790
Or I can...

274
00:31:47,790 --> 00:31:51,070
call you in the evening when you can't sleep.

275
00:31:57,420 --> 00:31:59,190
I'm not a strange person.

276
00:31:59,190 --> 00:32:01,250
My experiences are certified. I have no problems with the law.

277
00:32:01,250 --> 00:32:05,400
And if you want, I can show you my ID.

278
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:09,820
Do you really want me to believe you now?

279
00:32:13,260 --> 00:32:17,020
Believing me or not,

280
00:32:17,020 --> 00:32:19,690
it's up to you.

281
00:32:25,020 --> 00:32:27,380
Now, my work is done.

282
00:32:31,630 --> 00:32:34,380
Gosh, they are all soggy now.
